    "\"\"\"\n",
    "Referrence code from the link:\n",
    "https://github.com/IsaacPatole/CartPole-v0-using-Q-learning-SARSA-and-DNN/blob/master/Qlearning_for_cartpole.py\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "class CartPoleQAgent():\n",
    "    def __init__(Tiber, buckets=(2, 2, 6, 6), number_episodes=175, min_lr=0.1, min_epsilon=0.1, discount=1.0, decay=25):\n",
    "        Tiber.buckets = buckets\n",
    "        Tiber.number_episodes = number_episodes\n",
    "        Tiber.min_lr = min_lr\n",
    "        Tiber.min_epsilon = min_epsilon\n",
    "        Tiber.discount = discount\n",
    "        Tiber.decay = decay\n",
    "        ##The variable Tiber represents the Self\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Tiber.env = gym.make('CartPole-v0')\n",
    "        ## set the environment using 'CartPole-v0'\n",
    "        Tiber.Q_table = np.zeros(Tiber.buckets + (Tiber.env.action_space.n,))\n",
    "        ## This is the action-value function being initialized to 0's\n",
    "        ## standard format is [position, velocity, angle, angular velocity]\n",
    "        Tiber.upper_bounds = [Tiber.env.observation_space.high[0], 0.5, Tiber.env.observation_space.high[2], math.radians(50) / 1.]\n",
    "        Tiber.lower_bounds = [Tiber.env.observation_space.low[0], -0.5, Tiber.env.observation_space.low[2], -math.radians(50) / 1.]\n",
    "        Tiber.steps = np.zeros(Tiber.number_episodes)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def discretize_state(Tiber, observations):\n",
    "        ## the discretize_state\n",
    "        ## the observations(tuple) is including four floats which are represents the current state of the environment as input\n",
    "        discretized = list()\n",
    "        for i in range(len(observations)):\n",
    "            scaling = ((observations[i] + abs(Tiber.lower_bounds[i])) / (Tiber.upper_bounds[i] - Tiber.lower_bounds[i]))\n",
    "        ## using the scaling,scale data into new values that are easier to compare\n",
    "        ## The abs() method returns the absolute value of the given number(Tiber.lower_bounds[i])\n",
    "            new_observations = int(round((Tiber.buckets[i] - 1) * scaling))\n",
    "            new_observations = min(Tiber.buckets[i] - 1, max(0, new_observations))\n",
    "            discretized.append(new_observations)\n",
    "        return tuple(discretized)## The tuple method is a collection which is ordered and unchangeable\n",
    "        ## The discretized(tuple) is including four non-negative interger which less than n, and n is the number in the same position in the buckets list\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def The_choose_action(Tiber, state):\n",
    "        ## the method The_choose_action return 0 or 1 as action\n",
    "        if (np.random.random() < Tiber.epsilon):\n",
    "            return Tiber.env.action_space.sample()\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return np.argmax(Tiber.Q_table[state])\n",
    "        ## The state(Tuple) is including four non-negative interger which are within the range of the bucket.\n",
    "        ## return 0 or 1 (interger) as output\n",
    "            \n",
    "    def get_action(Tiber, state, e):\n",
    "        ## using another policy (epsilon greedy), assuming that the state not discretized\n",
    "        ## return the vertor with the problities for each action.\n",
    "        observations = Tiber.discretize_state(state)\n",
    "        The_act_vector = Tiber.Q_table[observations]\n",
    "        epsilon = Tiber.get_epsilon(e)\n",
    "        The_act_vector = Tiber.normalize(The_act_vector, epsilon)\n",
    "        return The_act_vector\n",
    "        ## The state(tuple) is including four floats which are represents the current state of the environment as input\n",
    "        ## The e(interger) AKA eplision represents the elision at which agent is supposed as input\n",
    "        ## return the The_act_vector(numpy.array). represents the vertor with the problities for each action.\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def normalize(Tiber, The_act_vector, epsilon):\n",
    "        total = sum(The_act_vector)\n",
    "        the_new_vector = (1-epsilon) * The_act_vector / (total)\n",
    "        the_new_vector += epsilon / 2.0\n",
    "        return the_new_vector\n",
    "        \n",
    "        ## The_act_vector(numpy.array),Contains the expected value of each action in the current state\n",
    "        ## epsilon(float) represents the chances that choose an action randomly by epsilon greedy\n",
    "        ##output, the_new_vector(numpy.array) represents the problities for each action which being chosen at the current state\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def update_q(Tiber, state, action, reward, new_state):\n",
    "        Tiber.Q_table[state][action] += Tiber.learning_rate * (reward + Tiber.discount * np.max(Tiber.Q_table[new_state]) - Tiber.Q_table[state][action])\n",
    "        ##Updates Q-table using the rule\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def get_epsilon(Tiber, t):\n",
    "        ##Gets value for epsilon. It declines as we advance in episodes.\n",
    "        return max(Tiber.min_epsilon, min(1., 1. - math.log10((t + 1) / Tiber.decay)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def get_learning_rate(Tiber, t):\n",
    "        ##Gets value for learning rate. It declines as we advance in episodes.\n",
    "        return max(Tiber.min_lr, min(1., 1. - math.log10((t + 1) / Tiber.decay)))    \n",
    "        \n",
    "    def train(Tiber):\n",
    "        ##Train the agent, make it through the environment and choose action\n",
    "        ##Through the E-greed policy and update its Q table values\n",
    "        ##The agent is trained by default for 800 episodes with a declining \n",
    "        ##learning rate and epsilon values that with the default values\n",
    "        ## Looping for each episode\n",
    "        for e in range(Tiber.number_episodes):\n",
    "            ## Initializes the state\n",
    "            current_state = Tiber.discretize_state(Tiber.env.reset())\n",
    "\n",
    "            Tiber.learning_rate = Tiber.get_learning_rate(e)\n",
    "            Tiber.epsilon = Tiber.get_epsilon(e)\n",
    "            done = False\n",
    "                \n",
    "        ## Looping for each step\n",
    "            while not done:\n",
    "                Tiber.steps[e] += 1\n",
    "                action = Tiber.The_choose_action(current_state)\n",
    "                observations, reward, done, _ = Tiber.env.step(action)\n",
    "                new_state = Tiber.discretize_state(observations)\n",
    "                Tiber.update_q(current_state, action, reward, new_state)\n",
    "                current_state = new_state\n",
    "\n",
    "        print('The trainning is completed!')\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def plot_learning(Tiber):\n",
    "        ## Draw the number of steps in each episode\n",
    "        ## print the amount of an episode  completes successfully\n",
    "        sns.lineplot(range(len(Tiber.steps)),Tiber.steps)\n",
    "        plt.xlabel(\"The Episode\")\n",
    "        plt.ylabel(\"The Steps\")\n",
    "        plt.show()\n",
    "        t = 0\n",
    "        for i in range(Tiber.number_episodes):\n",
    "            if Tiber.steps[i] == 200:\n",
    "                t+=1\n",
    "        print(t, \"The episodes were successfully completed!\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "    def run(Tiber):\n",
    "        Tiber.env = gym.wrappers.Monitor(Tiber.env,'cartpole')\n",
    "        t = 0\n",
    "        done = False\n",
    "        current_state = Tiber.discretize_state(Tiber.env.reset())\n",
    "        while not done:\n",
    "            Tiber.env.render()\n",
    "            t = t+1\n",
    "            action = Tiber.The_choose_action(current_state)\n",
    "            observations, reward, done, _ = Tiber.env.step(action)\n",
    "            new_state = Tiber.discretize_state(observations)\n",
    "            current_state = new_state\n",
    "            \n",
    "        return t\n",
    "    \n",
    "def load_Q_learning():\n",
    "    agent = CartPoleQAgent()\n",
    "    agent.train()\n",
    "    agent.plot_learning()\n",
    "\n",
    "    return agent\n",
    "\n",
    "agent = load_Q_learning()            \n",
    "            \n",
    "                           \n",
    "        "
   ]
